cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SY

This paper deals with audio signal processing and clustering, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). However, the paper also discusses natural language processing tasks such as spoken term detection, which could place it under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of Siamese networks and unsupervised learning methods suggests a focus on machine learning, which could place it under cs.SI (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses handling unbalanced data distribution, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper's focus on clustering and adjacency relationships could place it under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
